        {
          "@type": "dctypes:Text",
          "format": "text/plain",
          "chars": "Honor\u00e9 Daumier (1808-1879) was a French painter, sculptor, and printmaker. Empathizing with Les Bons Bourgeois (the urban middle class), Daumier critically depicted the tumultuous sociopolitical climate in France during the nineteenth century through his lithographs."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "@context": "http://iiif.io/api/presentation/2/context.json",
      "@id": "http://6bb7af80-f61a-4e38-9692-850a3ddf1a0a/annotation/1",
